participating-org.narrative:
Alternatives Espaces Citoyens was founded in Niger in September 2001. The initiator was Groupe Alternative, an NGO working on culture and the media and connected to the journal Alternative. Alternatives Espaces Citoyens fights for democratic values through civil education. For this purpose, it uses its radio station in Niamey, and its so-called study centres spread all over the country.
Vision : a society based on the values of democracy, social justice, solidarity and preservation of the environment, where fundamental freedoms , human rights , equity and equality between men and women are scrupulously respected .

The association aims to " work towards the emergence of an open, democratic and social society , based on equality of human rights, a new partnership between men and women, solidarity between people in an healthy environment. "

The objectives of the association are:
- promote, defend and contributeto the effectiveness of fundamental human rights and individual and collective freedoms ;
- build spaces of resistance, convergenceof social movements and alternatives to neoliberal policies ;
- Develop initiatives for citizen control of public action at national and local levels;
- Promote the rights, citizen participation and empowerment of women and vulnerable groups;
- contribute to the improvement of the environment and the protection of public goods , particularly water , forests , land and genetic endowment;
- Promote access , development and innovative use of media and information technologies and communication .

Alternatives Espaces Citoyens is a major actor in the emerging critical wing of the civil society of Niger.  Alternatives Espaces Citoyens is the co-initiator of the Social Forum of Niger (FSN), and manages its secretariat.
